Retrieves a list of enzyme-substrate resources available in OmniPath

Source: R/import.R
get_enzsub_resources.Rd

Get the names of the enzyme-substrate relationship resources available in http://omnipath.org/enzsub

get_enzsub_resources(dataset = NULL)

get_ptms_databases(...)

Arguments

dataset

ignored for this query type
...

Passed to get_enzsub_resources.

Value

character vector with the names of the enzyme-substrate resources

See also

get_resources, import_omnipath_enzsub

Examples

get_enzsub_resources()

#>  [1] "BEL-Large-Corpus_ProtMapper" "dbPTM"                      
#>  [3] "DEPOD"                       "HPRD"                       
#>  [5] "HPRD_MIMP"                   "KEA"                        
#>  [7] "Li2012"                      "MIMP"                       
#>  [9] "NCI-PID_ProtMapper"          "phosphoELM"                 
#> [11] "phosphoELM_MIMP"             "PhosphoNetworks"            
#> [13] "PhosphoSite"                 "PhosphoSite_MIMP"           
#> [15] "PhosphoSite_ProtMapper"      "ProtMapper"                 
#> [17] "REACH_ProtMapper"            "Reactome_ProtMapper"        
#> [19] "RLIMS-P_ProtMapper"          "SIGNOR"                     
#> [21] "SIGNOR_ProtMapper"           "Sparser_ProtMapper"
